The paper deals with compressive sensing and sparse reconstruction, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of a Gaussian mixture density for modeling the distribution of the source suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) approach. The analysis of upper- and lower-bounds on reconstruction error performance is a common theme in optimization (cs.MM) and statistics (cs.SI).
